WEBVTT

00:01.318 --> 00:02.259
<i> THONY: Previously</i>
<i> on "The Cleaning Lady"...</i>

00:03.062 --> 00:04.819
<i> You've been there a year now</i>
<i> since that donor backed out.</i>

00:05.006 --> 00:06.488
We're on
a donor registry, Marco.

00:06.899 --> 00:07.748
We just have to be patient.

00:08.234 --> 00:09.341
He sent me your visa.

00:09.493 --> 00:11.326
It's expired.
I'm afraid we can't help you.

00:11.345 --> 00:12.402
Check it out.

00:12.421 --> 00:14.588
Your daughter's
gonna love it, Theo.

00:14.664 --> 00:16.181
I'm just a cleaning lady.

00:16.333 --> 00:18.017
I can help you
make this disappear.

00:18.093 --> 00:19.426
Police have ID'd Theo's body.

00:19.503 --> 00:21.353
I-I still have
a cleaner inside.

00:21.505 --> 00:23.063
The cleaner
who should already be dead?

00:25.192 --> 00:27.175
-Do you trust me?
-Yeah.

00:27.194 --> 00:28.101
(screams)

00:28.254 --> 00:29.419
Where'd you learn
how to do that?

00:29.438 --> 00:30.845
What are you--some kind
of doctor or something?

00:30.865 --> 00:33.532
You want me to work
for you, protect me.

00:33.609 --> 00:35.534
-I give you my word.
-PERSON: That's her.

00:35.611 --> 00:37.202
<i> PERSON 2: I'm calling</i>
<i> to schedule an appointment</i>

00:37.354 --> 00:38.445
<i> for Luca.</i>

00:38.522 --> 00:40.113
Thank you for calling
the clinic for my son.

00:40.266 --> 00:41.281
I want you on call.

00:41.433 --> 00:42.933
This is your pay
for the other night

00:42.935 --> 00:44.209
and a burner phone.

00:44.361 --> 00:45.693
Why do you want me
to work for you?

00:45.771 --> 00:47.421
'Cause I don't want to
have to kill you.

00:49.884 --> 00:52.676
(indistinct chatter)

00:56.799 --> 00:59.475
LUCA:
It's supposed to make noise.

01:00.728 --> 01:05.122
(imitates rocket whooshing)
Incoming.

01:05.140 --> 01:07.215
Your dinosaur has
no chance now.

01:07.234 --> 01:10.527
(imitates rocket whooshing)

01:12.907 --> 01:14.073
(imitates gun firing)

01:14.224 --> 01:16.558
-Got ya!
-(laughter)

01:16.577 --> 01:19.495
Okay, you drink it now.

01:20.897 --> 01:22.581
We got to go, Thony.

01:22.658 --> 01:23.974
Yeah.

01:23.976 --> 01:26.143
All right, peanut,
time for me to go to work

01:26.161 --> 01:27.160
and you take a nap.

01:27.237 --> 01:28.812
I don't want to take a nap.

01:28.814 --> 01:31.148
But astronauts
need their sleep

01:31.166 --> 01:33.817
to become big and strong.

01:33.819 --> 01:37.054
-Okay, Mommy.
-All right.

01:38.657 --> 01:40.081
<i> MAN ON RADIO:</i>
<i> Good morning, Vegas.</i>

01:40.101 --> 01:43.435
<i> Here's a little something</i>
<i> to start your day.</i>

01:43.587 --> 01:46.421
W-where are my keys?
I-I know I put them here.

01:46.498 --> 01:49.090
-Chris has them.
-What? Why?

01:49.110 --> 01:50.642
He's just going
around the block

01:50.794 --> 01:51.852
He's not old enough to drive.

01:51.928 --> 01:54.504
Actually, he is.

01:54.506 --> 01:56.189
THONY:
I'm out of Luca's medicine.

01:56.266 --> 01:57.841
The guy I buy from
hasn't called me back.

01:57.860 --> 01:59.676
Can we swing
by his place after work?

01:59.695 --> 02:01.511
Well, we can't even
get to work

02:01.513 --> 02:03.697
because Chris is driving my van
around Vegas without a license.

02:03.773 --> 02:05.124
JAZ:
You don't have one either, Mom.

02:05.200 --> 02:07.517
-Stay calm.
-(mutters softly)

02:07.536 --> 02:09.110
-(keys jingling)
-Oh, you...

02:09.130 --> 02:10.945
What the hell
are you thinking, huh?

02:11.023 --> 02:12.798
You can't drive without me.

02:12.949 --> 02:16.209
You won't even sign
my driver's ed form.

02:16.286 --> 02:19.638
<i> (music playing indistinctly</i>
<i> on radio)</i>

02:19.789 --> 02:23.533
Mom, I said sign it,
not use it as a coaster.

02:23.535 --> 02:25.460
Well, I can't now because
we're going to be late,

02:25.537 --> 02:26.386
thanks to you.

02:26.463 --> 02:28.889
-Bye.
-JAZ: Have fun at work.

02:29.041 --> 02:32.225
<i> (thankyouverymuch's</i>
<i> "Good Vibes")</i>

02:32.378 --> 02:34.486
(bowling pins clatter)

02:34.638 --> 02:37.547
(cheers and laughter)

02:37.566 --> 02:39.324
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:39.476 --> 02:42.219
Hi, Ronnie.
This is Thony again.

02:42.221 --> 02:45.647
Um, I'm of the antivirals
for my son.

02:45.666 --> 02:48.667
His immune system is too weak.
He won't make it without it.

02:48.818 --> 02:50.318
Can you call me back, please?

02:50.396 --> 02:53.747
-Thank you.
-That guy still ghosting you?

02:53.899 --> 02:55.990
Yeah. It's getting harder
and harder

02:56.010 --> 02:58.493
to get all of the different
medicines he needs.

02:58.512 --> 03:01.905
Yeah, but the stem cell
trial starts soon, right?

03:01.924 --> 03:03.348
Not for another week.

03:03.500 --> 03:05.575
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:05.594 --> 03:08.245
FIONA: Yet some kids
get all the luck.

03:08.247 --> 03:11.356
Can you believe all those gifts
are just for one little brat?

03:12.434 --> 03:15.360
Oi, think they're gonna
leave that cake?

03:16.530 --> 03:19.364
I think you've got
a pretty good shot.

03:19.516 --> 03:21.441
Mm-hmm.
(laughs)

03:21.593 --> 03:23.184
<i> PERSON OVER PA:</i>
<i> Hey, boys and girls,</i>

03:23.262 --> 03:24.536
<i> it's time</i>
<i> for Timmy's birthday.</i>

03:24.688 --> 03:25.853
(stammering, clicks tongue)

03:25.873 --> 03:27.522
<i> -Please join us in lane 8.</i>
-FIONA: Score!

03:27.541 --> 03:30.525
There's a blocked toilet
in the women's bathroom.

03:30.544 --> 03:37.290
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:37.367 --> 03:41.253
-Ah! Wish me luck.
-FIONA: Good luck.

03:41.405 --> 03:44.114
(giggling)

03:44.116 --> 03:45.449
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:45.467 --> 03:47.976
(grunts)

03:53.901 --> 03:55.976
Hello? Hello?

03:56.128 --> 03:59.053
-Hello?
-Hi.

03:59.073 --> 04:01.740
Uh, sorry, is it okay
if I change my baby in here?

04:01.891 --> 04:05.302
There's no changing tables
in the men's bathroom.

04:05.320 --> 04:06.894
Yeah, it's over there.

04:06.972 --> 04:08.563
But watch your step.
The floor is wet.

04:08.582 --> 04:10.991
-Okay, thank you
-Mm-hmm.

04:11.143 --> 04:12.492
(grunts)

04:12.644 --> 04:15.979
I mean, what do they think us
woke dads are gonna do, huh?

04:15.998 --> 04:17.664
Change our babies
on the slot machines?

04:17.741 --> 04:21.242
(chuckles) Can you imagine the
germs on those things?

04:21.262 --> 04:22.344
Yikes!

04:24.765 --> 04:26.914
You got kids?

04:26.934 --> 04:30.752
Yeah, a boy.
He's five years old.

04:30.829 --> 04:34.547
Oh, me too. He's, uh--
he's just--he's bowling.

04:34.699 --> 04:36.182
Uh, where are you from?

04:36.335 --> 04:38.426
I-I, uh, can't quite place
the accent.

04:38.504 --> 04:41.280
Wait. Hold on, hold on.
Don't tell me. Let me guess.

04:41.431 --> 04:43.431
-New Jersey?
-(chuckles)

04:43.450 --> 04:46.100
Close.
Cambodia.

04:46.120 --> 04:47.619
-PERSON: Oh, so close.
-(chuckles)

04:47.771 --> 04:50.122
-(baby cooing)
-Oh, I know.

04:50.198 --> 04:51.623
I know.
You're all better.

04:51.775 --> 04:53.366
Sorry, I have to--
I have to wash my hands.

04:53.519 --> 04:55.702
-Do you mind?
-Oh, it's okay.

04:55.854 --> 04:58.371
All right.
There you go.

04:58.524 --> 05:00.373
(baby fusses)

05:00.526 --> 05:03.860
THONY: Hello.
What's your name?

05:03.879 --> 05:06.972
-Sarah.
-Hello, Sarah.

05:10.126 --> 05:12.869
And I'm Garrett.
Garrett Miller.

05:12.888 --> 05:14.888
Thony.

05:14.964 --> 05:16.389
De La Rosa.

05:16.542 --> 05:20.377
<i> (tense music)</i>

05:20.379 --> 05:23.229
I wanted to approach you
in a safe place.

05:23.382 --> 05:25.382
Uh, I'm an FBI Special Agent.

05:25.384 --> 05:28.118
I just have
a few questions for you.

05:29.979 --> 05:32.906
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

05:32.982 --> 05:37.911
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:37.987 --> 05:39.579
So Alonzo...

05:39.656 --> 05:41.398
your supervisor, said
you worked at the warehouse

05:41.416 --> 05:42.824
the night
that Theo went missing.

05:42.843 --> 05:45.010
-Did you know him well?
-No.

05:45.161 --> 05:47.679
Uh, I only worked
for him three weeks.

05:47.831 --> 05:50.832
Okay, but you were close enough
to go to his funeral,

05:50.851 --> 05:53.410
and then you gave
his daughter a gift?

05:53.428 --> 05:56.855
Yeah.
Theo was a single dad.

05:56.932 --> 06:01.843
And he didn't know what to get
for a 16-year-old girl,

06:01.862 --> 06:04.196
so he asked for my help.

06:04.347 --> 06:06.923
I wanted to make sure
she got it.

06:06.925 --> 06:13.747
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:15.617 --> 06:17.784
This way, gentlemen.

06:17.936 --> 06:20.770
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:20.789 --> 06:22.196
All right, here's the hardware

06:22.216 --> 06:24.383
we've been talking about,
all right?

06:24.534 --> 06:26.776
AKs, AR-15s, RPGs,

06:26.795 --> 06:29.388
and, uh, three dozen Barretts.

06:29.539 --> 06:36.119
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:36.138 --> 06:39.122
(speaking Armenian)

06:39.141 --> 06:42.216
(speaking in Armenian)

06:42.294 --> 06:44.461
You know, more snipers
and assassins come from Armenia

06:44.463 --> 06:47.147
than anywhere else
in the world.

06:47.299 --> 06:48.723
Roman is our very best.

06:48.742 --> 06:50.742
Then he should have the best.

06:50.894 --> 06:54.228
-How does it feel, Roman?
-Good.

06:54.248 --> 06:57.707
(softly speaking Armenian)

06:59.478 --> 07:01.628
You gentlemen
take your time.

07:03.590 --> 07:06.633
(both speaking Spanish)

07:19.998 --> 07:21.255
We have a thief.

07:21.275 --> 07:23.424
Do we have a problem, Arman?

07:23.502 --> 07:25.110
No. No, let's head up
to the office.

07:25.187 --> 07:26.260
We'll discuss some numbers.

07:26.280 --> 07:29.364
(people arguing in Armenian)

07:33.028 --> 07:37.847
(both speaking Spanish)

07:37.849 --> 07:40.942
You think you can
short me my guns?

07:40.961 --> 07:42.610
Hayak gave me his word.

07:42.688 --> 07:44.463
Viktor, all we need is a couple
days to complete the shipment.

07:44.614 --> 07:46.539
We're fighting a war
for our homeland!

07:46.616 --> 07:49.951
Armenia doesn't have days!
Every second counts!

07:50.028 --> 07:52.119
(shouting in Armenian)

07:52.139 --> 07:55.140
(both speaking Spanish)

07:55.217 --> 07:57.142
Viktor, hey, hey.
Calm down.

07:57.219 --> 07:59.644
Don't tell me to calm down!

07:59.796 --> 08:01.538
-Don't tell me!
-Hey.

08:01.556 --> 08:03.631
No, no, no, no.
(speaking in Spanish)

08:03.650 --> 08:06.651
(overlapping shouting)

08:08.155 --> 08:09.546
Hey.
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

08:09.564 --> 08:11.397
Hey, hey.
We're gonna work this out.

08:11.474 --> 08:12.473
Nobody's trying
to cheat you here.

08:12.493 --> 08:14.659
This is not
a problem, Viktor.

08:14.811 --> 08:16.477
We can get your guns,
all right?

08:16.555 --> 08:19.313
-(speaking Spanish)
-(people shouting in Armenian)

08:19.391 --> 08:21.500
Let's talk about this.
Come on, Viktor, let's--

08:25.413 --> 08:27.731
Hey!

08:27.749 --> 08:29.566
Enough!

08:29.584 --> 08:31.843
This ends now.

08:31.920 --> 08:35.755
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:35.832 --> 08:37.182
I said we're gonna
get you the guns,

08:37.333 --> 08:39.759
and we're gonna do that!

08:39.911 --> 08:41.836
All we need is
a couple of days.

08:41.855 --> 08:43.855
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:43.932 --> 08:46.191
You have 24 hours...

08:46.342 --> 08:48.843
or there will be
more bloodshed.

08:48.862 --> 08:55.575
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:59.097 --> 09:01.781
You ever see any of these guys
at the warehouse?

09:01.933 --> 09:07.712
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:07.789 --> 09:09.214
Just say when.

09:09.291 --> 09:10.698
Hmm?

09:10.717 --> 09:12.442
-No.
-No? You sure?

09:12.460 --> 09:14.702
Take your time.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.279
-FIONA: Thony?
-Yeah.

09:16.298 --> 09:17.614
Oh.

09:17.632 --> 09:19.132
Hey, thank you, uh,

09:19.208 --> 09:21.117
for letting
me change her diaper.

09:21.119 --> 09:22.635
-I appreciate it.
-You're welcome

09:22.788 --> 09:24.120
Okay.

09:24.122 --> 09:26.398
FIONA:
Hi.

09:30.145 --> 09:32.553
He's hot.
(giggles)

09:32.631 --> 09:34.406
Another party just cleared out.
Let's go.

09:34.557 --> 09:38.134
-Okay, I'm almost done here.
-Okay.

09:38.153 --> 09:41.121
(cell phone ringing)

09:43.399 --> 09:44.398
Yeah?

09:44.418 --> 09:46.751
I'm sending a driver
to pick you up.

09:46.828 --> 09:49.403
<i> -THONY: I am at work.</i>
-Text me the address.

09:49.423 --> 09:55.076
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:55.095 --> 09:56.928
All right, wait, wait.

09:57.080 --> 10:02.601
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:02.752 --> 10:04.919
(speaking in Spanish)

10:04.996 --> 10:11.425
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:11.445 --> 10:12.986
All right. Go on..

10:15.282 --> 10:18.074
I want him buried
at Greenwood.

10:20.287 --> 10:21.845
And, Carlos, when you find out

10:21.863 --> 10:24.122
who's been stealing
our merchandise,

10:24.199 --> 10:26.349
I want you
to bring him to me.

10:26.368 --> 10:31.204
All right, I don't want him to
know Mateo's death is on him.

10:31.280 --> 10:34.090
-You got it, boss.
-All right.

10:41.867 --> 10:43.716
Clean this up
as soon as possible.

10:43.869 --> 10:45.644
I let the warehouse staff
go for the rest of the day.

10:45.720 --> 10:48.963
Told them there was a gas leak
so they won't bother you.

10:48.982 --> 10:50.357
Wait.

10:53.378 --> 10:54.986
After I finish here today,

10:55.063 --> 10:58.323
I want out of, um,
our arrangement.

10:58.474 --> 11:01.067
You want to call
the shots now?

11:01.219 --> 11:02.810
I came to this country
to save my son.

11:02.829 --> 11:05.121
I can't be involved
in any of this.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.334
You have to let me go.

11:09.485 --> 11:13.338
Sure. Yeah, go.

11:13.489 --> 11:15.415
You can go.

11:15.491 --> 11:17.175
But the second
you're out on your own,

11:17.326 --> 11:18.659
I can no longer protect you.

11:18.679 --> 11:20.327
You couldn't even
protect Mateo.

11:20.347 --> 11:22.255
How do you expect
to protect me?

11:22.407 --> 11:29.145
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:35.178 --> 11:37.420
Just do your job...

11:37.439 --> 11:40.423
so I can justify
keeping you alive.

11:40.483 --> 11:47.455
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:03.965 --> 12:06.950
<i> (hip-hop music)</i>

12:06.952 --> 12:13.982
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:16.795 --> 12:18.644
<i> RAPPER: ♪ Let all the fears</i>
<i> just wash away ♪</i>

12:18.797 --> 12:19.979
<i> ♪ Time to wipe the tears ♪</i>

12:20.131 --> 12:22.648
<i> ♪ Stronger version</i>
<i> of me here today ♪</i>

12:22.801 --> 12:24.650
<i> ♪ I got to clean up</i>
<i> all the mess I made ♪</i>

12:24.803 --> 12:27.912
<i> ♪ Plus, I told myself</i>
<i> that there'll be better days ♪</i>

12:28.064 --> 12:29.322
<i> ♪ Than yesterday ♪</i>

12:29.474 --> 12:30.915
<i> ♪ I live today</i>
<i> like it's the final day ♪</i>

12:31.067 --> 12:32.325
<i> ♪ Got to make a way ♪</i>

12:32.401 --> 12:34.919
<i> ♪ And from the wave,</i>
<i> I never float away ♪</i>

12:34.996 --> 12:37.647
<i> ♪ I'll never fade</i>
<i> or wipe the pain away ♪</i>

12:37.665 --> 12:39.073
<i> ♪ Look me in my eyes ♪</i>

12:39.092 --> 12:41.426
<i> ♪ And you'll see bravery</i>
<i> from miles away ♪</i>

12:41.503 --> 12:44.320
<i> ♪ I feel it</i>
<i> in my bloodstream ♪</i>

12:44.339 --> 12:47.340
<i> ♪ I keep swimming upstream ♪</i>

12:47.492 --> 12:49.842
<i> ♪ I'm running</i>
<i> on a balance beam ♪</i>

12:49.995 --> 12:53.772
<i> ♪ But everything around me</i>
<i> isn't what they seem ♪</i>

12:53.848 --> 12:56.441
<i> ♪ I feel it</i>
<i> in my bloodstream ♪</i>

12:56.518 --> 12:58.443
<i> SINGERS:</i>
<i> ♪ Feel it in my bloodstream ♪</i>

12:58.520 --> 13:02.688
<i> ♪ And I'm about</i>
<i> to lose myself tonight ♪</i>

13:02.841 --> 13:05.617
<i> ♪ Always on the upstream ♪</i>

13:05.693 --> 13:08.845
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:08.863 --> 13:10.530
What are you doing here?

13:10.682 --> 13:13.941
I thought they sent everybody
home 'cause of the gas leak.

13:14.019 --> 13:16.185
I'm--I'm just here to clean.

13:16.204 --> 13:18.538
They asked me to come back.

13:18.690 --> 13:20.356
Oh.

13:20.358 --> 13:21.374
Okay.

13:21.526 --> 13:24.377
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

13:24.529 --> 13:30.308
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:30.459 --> 13:33.386
<i> (Dean Martin's "Ain't</i>
<i> That a Kick in the Head")</i>

13:33.538 --> 13:37.723
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:37.800 --> 13:41.544
<i> DEAN MARTIN:</i>
<i> ♪ How lucky can one guy be? ♪</i>

13:41.546 --> 13:45.064
<i> ♪ I kissed her,</i>
<i> and she kissed me ♪</i>

13:45.216 --> 13:47.383
<i> ♪ Like the fella once said ♪</i>

13:47.385 --> 13:50.053
<i> ♪ "Ain't that a kick</i>
<i> in the head?" ♪</i>

13:50.071 --> 13:52.497
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:52.574 --> 13:56.059
<i> ♪ Her room</i>
<i> was completely black ♪</i>

13:56.061 --> 13:59.320
<i> ♪ I hugged her,</i>
<i> and she hugged back ♪</i>

13:59.397 --> 14:01.581
<i> ♪ Like the sailor said,</i>
<i> quote ♪</i>

14:01.733 --> 14:05.251
<i> ♪ "Ain't that a hole</i>
<i> in the boat?" ♪</i>

14:05.403 --> 14:08.421
<i> ♪ My head keeps spinning ♪</i>

14:08.497 --> 14:11.182
<i> ♪ I go to sleep</i>
<i> and keep grinning ♪</i>

14:11.334 --> 14:13.926
-Good afternoon, Mr. Morales.
-ARMAN: How you doing?

14:14.003 --> 14:16.020
<i> DEAN MARTIN:</i>
<i> ♪ Just the beginning ♪</i>

14:16.097 --> 14:18.915
<i> ♪ My life is gonna be... ♪</i>

14:18.933 --> 14:21.267
Good afternoon.

14:21.419 --> 14:24.087
-Good to see you.
-Hey.

14:24.089 --> 14:26.756
-How you doing?
-Enjoy your lunch.

14:26.774 --> 14:29.942
Cheers. Enjoy.

14:30.019 --> 14:31.685
<i> -Gracias.</i>
<i> -De nada.</i>

14:31.705 --> 14:34.021
<i>Hola, guapo.</i>

14:34.040 --> 14:36.357
All set for Councilman Knight?

14:36.376 --> 14:38.692
-You mean Mr. Moocher?
-(sighs) Don't call him that.

14:38.712 --> 14:42.288
He's over there, enjoying
the beluga caviar he demanded

14:42.365 --> 14:44.774
while waiting for you--
moocher.

14:44.792 --> 14:48.127
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:48.279 --> 14:50.680
Babe, what's wrong?

14:54.636 --> 14:56.269
Mateo's dead.

14:57.305 --> 14:58.712
<i> ¿Qué?</i>

14:58.732 --> 15:00.214
Took a bullet for me.

15:00.291 --> 15:03.234
<i> Ay, Dios mío.</i>
What happened?

15:03.386 --> 15:04.569
We were missing some guns.

15:04.720 --> 15:06.646
The buyer thought we were
trying to cheat him.

15:06.798 --> 15:08.965
He--he just lost it.

15:08.967 --> 15:11.300
So now I need
this guy's help.

15:11.319 --> 15:14.228
(scoffs) Haven't we put enough
in pockets already?

15:14.305 --> 15:16.915
You know how it is, babe.
It's Vegas politics.

15:17.066 --> 15:19.142
He's the man
with the contacts.

15:19.160 --> 15:20.643
Yeah, I know.

15:20.662 --> 15:23.755
<i> (upbeat electronic music)</i>

15:23.831 --> 15:30.653
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:30.655 --> 15:32.913
Get him some more caviar,
would you?

15:32.933 --> 15:36.417
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:36.436 --> 15:39.086
-Eric.
-Oh, hey!

15:39.164 --> 15:41.514
-How you doing?
-Arman, my man!

15:41.666 --> 15:42.756
(grunts)

15:42.834 --> 15:43.983
Hey, you can take me

15:47.096 --> 15:48.262
You think you can set me up

15:48.281 --> 15:50.006
with that hot little
piece of ass?

15:50.024 --> 15:51.432
Her name's Lexi.

15:51.451 --> 15:53.526
I can make an introduction,
but no promises.

15:53.678 --> 15:55.620
Have a seat.

15:57.182 --> 15:59.440
So, Eric, we're gonna need
a little more time

15:59.459 --> 16:01.367
to get our funds together
to purchase this hotel.

16:01.519 --> 16:04.854
-How much more time you need?
-A week.

16:04.856 --> 16:07.373
I'll see what I can do.

16:07.525 --> 16:09.676
Let me ask you a question.

16:11.529 --> 16:15.156
Why is Hayak so hot
to buy this hotel anyhow?

16:15.233 --> 16:17.809
-The club's here.
-(laughs)

16:17.960 --> 16:19.727
Yeah?
That's good.

16:21.464 --> 16:24.482
What do you guys do,
really?

16:24.633 --> 16:25.650
Just--

16:25.801 --> 16:27.652
'Cause I think...

16:27.803 --> 16:31.897
you want to launder money
through the casino.

16:31.974 --> 16:34.975
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

16:35.053 --> 16:36.828
Details you
shouldn't know, Eric.

16:36.979 --> 16:37.978
Enjoy your lunch.

16:37.998 --> 16:40.723
We'll talk more
when Hayak gets back.

16:40.725 --> 16:42.316
Oh, I will.

16:42.393 --> 16:43.710
Mmm.

16:45.063 --> 16:48.006
Hmm. Mmm.

16:50.844 --> 16:53.736
Fi, it's a raid!
Run! Run!

16:53.755 --> 16:54.846
What?

16:54.997 --> 16:57.849
(indistinct shouting)

16:58.000 --> 17:04.731
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:12.389 --> 17:13.939
-PERSON: Okay.
-(person 2 whistles)

17:14.016 --> 17:15.349
Everybody, hold on, calm down.

17:15.426 --> 17:18.594
-This is not a raid, all right?
-Whoa, slow down.

17:18.613 --> 17:21.931
As I said, this is not a raid.
We are not ICE.

17:21.949 --> 17:25.117
We are the FBI.

17:25.270 --> 17:26.786
We just have
a few questions for you.

17:26.862 --> 17:33.534
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:33.611 --> 17:35.595
(cell phone chimes)

17:47.216 --> 17:49.809
Alonzo told us
you're Thony's sister-in-law.

17:49.961 --> 17:51.627
Uh, yes.

17:51.629 --> 17:55.222
Um, she's--she's
married to my brother.

17:55.241 --> 17:59.368
Wait, weren't you with Thony
in--in the bathroom earlier?

18:00.563 --> 18:03.230
Did Thony--
did Thony ever say anything

18:03.308 --> 18:05.324
about the night
she worked at the warehouse?

18:05.401 --> 18:09.253
No. I-I mean, I-I knew
she was working there, but--

18:09.330 --> 18:11.147
-What time did Thony come home?
-Late.

18:11.165 --> 18:13.649
But fight nights
always run late, so...

18:13.668 --> 18:14.675
Hmm.

18:17.413 --> 18:20.014
You ever seen any of the men
in these photos?

18:23.344 --> 18:25.586
-ALONZO: You can't go--
-THONY: Fi.

18:25.663 --> 18:27.754
ALONZO:
Stop, Thony.

18:27.774 --> 18:29.348
Sorry.
I told her not to come in.

18:29.500 --> 18:30.850
-(cell phone rings)
-Oh, she's fine.

18:31.002 --> 18:32.017
Thanks, Alonzo.

18:32.094 --> 18:33.686
What are you doing back here?

18:33.762 --> 18:36.856
Oh, just getting to know
some of your coworkers.

18:36.932 --> 18:40.192
No. You're using scare tactics
on vulnerable people,

18:40.345 --> 18:42.286
making everyone think
they're getting deported.

18:42.479 --> 18:46.182
Hmm, is that what you two
are worried about?

18:46.200 --> 18:48.684
'Cause I see here
that you are--

18:48.686 --> 18:51.778
oh, you are
both undocumented.

18:51.798 --> 18:53.856
In fact, Fiona has been
in this country illegally

18:53.875 --> 18:56.467
for, what, 15 years?

18:58.120 --> 19:00.379
Look, I already
told Fiona this.

19:00.531 --> 19:02.381
We just want information
about the night

19:02.533 --> 19:05.217
that you were
at the warehouse, okay?

19:05.294 --> 19:06.719
So, if you're ready
to open up,

19:06.871 --> 19:10.481
then we won't have to question
your sister-in-law anymore.

19:10.633 --> 19:13.151
Now, she said you got home
pretty late that night.

19:13.302 --> 19:16.154
No, no, tha--that's not
what I said.

19:16.230 --> 19:18.156
(sighs)
We've told you what we know.

19:18.307 --> 19:20.992
(cell phone ringing)

19:24.055 --> 19:25.479
You need to get that?

19:25.556 --> 19:28.541
I'll call back when we're done,
which is now.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.155
(Garrett chuckles)

19:35.175 --> 19:38.158
She's a little spitfire, huh?

19:38.178 --> 19:40.327
You were in the bathroom
with her?

19:40.405 --> 19:42.346
I mean, I-I was just making
first contact.

19:42.498 --> 19:44.407
-It was harmless.
-Listen, Garrett.

19:44.425 --> 19:46.242
Unless you want to go back
on the bench

19:46.244 --> 19:47.668
for another indiscretion,

19:47.687 --> 19:51.580
someone goes with you when
you question a female witness.

19:51.599 --> 19:54.675
-Period.
-Mm-hmm. I was with someone.

19:54.694 --> 19:55.610
-My kids.
-Oh.

19:57.197 --> 19:58.437
with my hands tied
behind my back,

19:58.589 --> 19:59.530
so just cut me some slack.

19:59.774 --> 20:02.591
Losing Theo as a CI
puts us back to square one.

20:02.610 --> 20:05.870
I know. But if Russo finds out
about your little stunt,

20:05.947 --> 20:07.521
she'll kick you off this case.

20:07.598 --> 20:10.933
I guess she doesn't have
to find out, now, does she?

20:10.952 --> 20:13.436
-(gasps)
-Hmm?

20:13.438 --> 20:17.215
Without an informant,
this case is already dead.

20:17.366 --> 20:23.471
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:28.394 --> 20:31.120
Fi. Fi, Fi, it's okay.
I'll drive.

20:31.138 --> 20:34.473
(crying, sniffles)

20:34.625 --> 20:37.810
I thought that was it, Thony.
I thought it was over.

20:37.962 --> 20:39.645
I know.

20:39.797 --> 20:40.887
Come here.

20:40.907 --> 20:42.298
It's okay.

20:42.316 --> 20:46.393
You're not getting
deported, okay?

20:46.412 --> 20:49.154
No, you don't know that.
You don't know that.

20:49.231 --> 20:53.567
I'm not just worried about me.
It--it's Chris, too.

20:53.586 --> 20:57.421
What do you mean Chris?
I thought he was born here.

20:57.498 --> 21:02.318
No. I-I-I didn't make it here
on time.

21:02.320 --> 21:04.578
But I never told anyone.
I mean, not even Chris.

21:04.597 --> 21:08.391
He thinks he's American,
but--but he's not.

21:10.270 --> 21:12.177
We're gonna
figure this out, okay?

21:12.330 --> 21:14.497
But you have to tell Chris.

21:14.515 --> 21:17.525
He can't find out
any other way.

21:18.927 --> 21:21.186
I know. I know.

21:21.339 --> 21:23.689
(cell phone ringing)

21:23.841 --> 21:24.782
(zipper opens)

21:24.859 --> 21:28.286
(ringing continues)

21:28.362 --> 21:31.530
-Jaz, what's up?
-I've been trying to call you.

21:31.607 --> 21:34.867
<i> -I think Luca's sick.</i>
-I'll be right back.

21:34.943 --> 21:35.942
Luca's sick.
We got to go.

21:36.020 --> 21:37.586
(zipper closes)

21:44.045 --> 21:47.029
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

21:47.048 --> 21:54.061
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:55.890 --> 21:57.631
When did you start
coughing, baby?

21:57.708 --> 22:01.635
This morning.
I forgot to tell someone.

22:01.654 --> 22:03.154
That's okay. We're here now.

22:03.230 --> 22:04.713
I want to talk to Daddy.

22:04.715 --> 22:06.398
Yeah, we're gonna call him.

22:06.551 --> 22:08.975
Open wide.

22:09.053 --> 22:10.995
That's a good boy.

22:13.333 --> 22:15.391
Tita Fi's gonna
call Daddy now.

22:15.393 --> 22:16.742
Okay.

22:16.894 --> 22:19.986
I'm gonna call that guy and see
if I can get this medicine.

22:20.006 --> 22:23.415
Okay. All right.
Let's call Daddy, huh?

22:23.492 --> 22:30.264
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:31.667 --> 22:35.001
<i> (line trilling)</i>

22:35.021 --> 22:35.928
<i> (line beeping)</i>

22:36.080 --> 22:37.521
<i> PERSON:</i>
<i> We're sorry.</i>

22:37.598 --> 22:40.149
<i> You have reached a number</i>
<i> that is no longer in service.</i>

22:42.195 --> 22:44.436
<i> (Marco singing indistinctly</i>
<i> on tablet)</i>

22:44.589 --> 22:45.846
<i> (line trilling)</i>

22:45.923 --> 22:50.259
<i> (continues singing</i>
<i> indistinctly)</i>

22:50.277 --> 22:52.595
<i> PERSON: Institute</i>
<i> of Stem Cell Medicine.</i>

22:52.613 --> 22:53.946
Hello, is this Helen?

22:54.098 --> 22:55.781
HELEN: Yes, it is.
How may I help you?

22:55.858 --> 22:57.541
<i> THONY: Oh, this is</i>
<i> Dr. Thony De La Rosa.</i>

22:57.618 --> 23:00.953
I have an appointment for
my son coming up soon, Luca.

23:01.105 --> 23:02.529
<i> He has</i>
<i> an immunodeficiency disorder.</i>

23:02.548 --> 23:04.289
I remember.
Dr. Saroyan referred you.

23:04.442 --> 23:05.883
Yes, that's right.

23:06.034 --> 23:10.279
Um, Luca got an infection, and,
uh, we are out of antivirals.

23:10.297 --> 23:12.114
I was wondering
if Dr. Christian

23:12.133 --> 23:13.465
could--could write
a prescription today.

23:13.559 --> 23:16.135
<i> HELEN: I'm sorry. She can't</i>
<i> prescribe any medication</i>

23:16.287 --> 23:18.120
<i> without first seeing</i>
<i> a patient.</i>

23:18.122 --> 23:20.564
<i> You should really go</i>
<i> to the E.R.</i>

23:22.551 --> 23:23.642
Yes, thank you.

23:23.719 --> 23:27.029
<i> (Marco continues singing</i>
<i> indistinctly)</i>

23:45.666 --> 23:48.575
(cell phone beeping)

23:48.594 --> 23:51.679
<i> (line trilling)</i>

23:53.266 --> 23:55.099
ERIC: It's mind-numbing,
really, these city meetings.

23:55.250 --> 23:56.434
You have no idea.

23:56.585 --> 23:58.160
If I have to sit

23:58.179 --> 24:00.587
through another traffic light
committee, I might kill myself.

24:00.606 --> 24:04.442
<i> (continues singing</i>
<i> indistinctly)</i>

24:04.593 --> 24:07.503
<i> (suspenseful music)</i>

24:07.521 --> 24:09.171
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:09.173 --> 24:11.574
(thermometer beeping)

24:12.843 --> 24:14.100
Okay, his temperature's rising.

24:14.120 --> 24:16.269
Marco, I'm gonna have
to take him to the E.R.

24:16.289 --> 24:17.771
I'll call you
from the hospital.

24:17.790 --> 24:21.107
<i> Be strong, Luca.</i>
<i> (speaks Tagalog)</i>

24:21.127 --> 24:22.518
The E.R.?

24:22.520 --> 24:25.612
Hey, you know you could
get deported, okay?

24:25.690 --> 24:26.947
It happened
to Samantha's cousin.

24:27.024 --> 24:28.632
She went to the E.R.
for a burst appendix,

24:28.784 --> 24:30.209
and then he woke up in Haiti.

24:30.361 --> 24:31.284
It happens.

24:31.304 --> 24:34.029
-Fi, I have no choice.
-No, no, no.

24:34.031 --> 24:36.699
Okay, I'm--I'm going
with you, then.

24:36.717 --> 24:39.977
No, no, no. There's no point in
both of us risking deportation.

24:40.128 --> 24:42.721
You have to stay here
for your kids.

24:42.798 --> 24:47.651
I know you're here, always,
no matter what happens.

24:47.803 --> 24:50.029
I'll get the kids
to say goodbye.

24:53.534 --> 24:55.141
You okay?

24:55.161 --> 24:58.387
(indistinct chatter)

24:58.405 --> 25:03.075
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:03.151 --> 25:06.128
-Children's Hospital.
-DRIVER: Sure.

25:08.733 --> 25:10.591
I'll call you, Fi.

25:19.243 --> 25:22.019
<i> GPS NAVIGATION:</i>
<i> In 30 feet, turn right.</i>

25:22.096 --> 25:25.231
(turn signal clicking)

25:30.087 --> 25:31.529
Wait.

25:33.366 --> 25:35.032
Make a left.

25:35.109 --> 25:37.943
<i> (hip-hop music)</i>

25:38.095 --> 25:40.112
May I present...

25:40.264 --> 25:43.690
the Cohiba Behike 52.

25:43.709 --> 25:47.503
Castro's favorite cigar.
They're handmade.

25:49.273 --> 25:51.790
Rolled between a woman's thighs

25:51.867 --> 25:55.368
until the tobacco leaves
are as soft as her skin.

25:55.388 --> 25:59.314
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:59.316 --> 26:01.725
Who could resist that?

26:01.802 --> 26:04.728
(elevator bell dings)

26:04.805 --> 26:08.315
(indistinct chatter)

26:20.395 --> 26:22.304
Ma'am?
Excuse me. Ma'am?

26:22.323 --> 26:25.332
(indistinct chatter,
laughter)

26:28.996 --> 26:31.997
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

26:32.149 --> 26:33.573
<i>¿Qué es esto?</i>

26:33.593 --> 26:35.500
Cover for me.

26:35.577 --> 26:41.640
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:42.827 --> 26:44.159
Ma'am. Ma'am.

26:44.178 --> 26:46.678
This is a private club.
I cannot allow you to go in.

26:46.831 --> 26:48.439
-Mr. Morales--
-It's all right.

26:48.515 --> 26:50.274
It's okay.
Come on, come on.

26:50.425 --> 26:52.425
(door closes)

26:52.445 --> 26:55.520
What the hell
are you doing here?

26:55.673 --> 26:57.156
He's dying.

27:03.864 --> 27:06.849
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

27:06.867 --> 27:13.797
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:13.949 --> 27:17.051
(camera shutter clicking)

27:20.865 --> 27:24.049
(engine turning over)

27:24.126 --> 27:27.394
(camera shutter clicking)

27:32.634 --> 27:39.239
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:44.330 --> 27:45.996
-I need to go with him.
-Don't worry.

27:46.115 --> 27:48.724
-Your son's in good hands.
-Thank you, Dr. Saroyan.

27:48.742 --> 27:50.292
Yeah, yeah.

28:00.662 --> 28:02.754
(door opens)

28:02.907 --> 28:05.741
(monitor beeping)

28:05.759 --> 28:08.001
(door closes)

28:08.020 --> 28:12.356
(ventilator whirring)

28:12.507 --> 28:14.024
Thank you.

28:20.032 --> 28:21.681
You don't have to stay.

28:21.759 --> 28:23.409
It might be a while.

28:25.946 --> 28:28.539
I have been where you are...

28:30.434 --> 28:32.710
With my father.

28:32.786 --> 28:36.046
(sighs) He used to work
for Hayak as his gardener

28:36.198 --> 28:39.550
until he collapsed on his lawn.

28:39.701 --> 28:42.202
It was his heart.

28:42.221 --> 28:43.295
He would have died

28:43.464 --> 28:46.598
if Hayak wouldn't have paid
for that surgery.

28:50.045 --> 28:52.971
That's why you started
working for him?

28:53.123 --> 28:54.973
Because you owed him?

28:55.125 --> 28:56.883
No, I was only 15 at the time.

28:56.902 --> 28:59.144
My parents made it really clear

28:59.296 --> 29:02.722
that I wasn't to work
for Hayak.

29:02.800 --> 29:04.816
They brought us
to this country

29:04.969 --> 29:07.494
to get us away from
the gang violence in Mexico.

29:09.139 --> 29:11.415
But you worked
for him anyway.

29:15.312 --> 29:16.920
I didn't want to have
to depend on anybody

29:17.072 --> 29:18.881
to protect my family.

29:20.092 --> 29:23.135
I swore I'd never be
in that position ever again.

29:29.769 --> 29:31.560
How's your father now?

29:35.775 --> 29:39.026
Ah, he hasn't spoken
to me in years.

29:41.522 --> 29:44.364
(cell phone vibrating)

29:47.511 --> 29:48.176
Yeah?

29:48.195 --> 29:49.435
<i> PERSON:</i>
<i> Hey, boss.</i>

29:49.513 --> 29:51.513
<i> We need you</i>
<i> at the truck depot.</i>

29:51.532 --> 29:52.998
I'll be right there.

30:06.138 --> 30:08.955
Hey.
You all right, Mom?

30:08.974 --> 30:10.456
I, um--
(scoffs)

30:10.534 --> 30:12.884
I forgot to pack
Thony's Buddha.

30:12.961 --> 30:15.962
(chuckles)
Mom, they'll be back.

30:16.040 --> 30:18.982
The doctor's not gonna
turn them in, right?

30:19.134 --> 30:20.892
'Cause when it comes
to stuff like this,

30:20.969 --> 30:24.880
sometimes you can be
a little dramatic.

30:24.898 --> 30:27.825
No.
No, Chris, I'm not.

30:27.976 --> 30:29.827
It's called
medical repatriation.

30:29.945 --> 30:31.570
-It's a thing. Google it.
-All right.

30:31.722 --> 30:32.979
No! No!

30:32.998 --> 30:34.981
We can never let
our guard down.

30:35.000 --> 30:36.149
All right, I get it, okay?

30:36.168 --> 30:39.561
No, I don't--
I don't think you do.

30:39.580 --> 30:41.839
Look, Mom, aren't we just
worried about Luca right now?

30:41.990 --> 30:44.066
No, no, Chris.
I'm...

30:44.084 --> 30:47.511
I'm--I'm worried
about you, okay?

30:47.662 --> 30:51.348
The reason why I can't sign
your--your driver's permit

30:51.425 --> 30:55.668
is because I-I don't have
your birth certificate.

30:55.746 --> 30:57.563
-You lost it?
-No.

30:58.916 --> 31:00.932
Um...

31:01.085 --> 31:02.876
you never had one.

31:02.953 --> 31:05.845
I lied.
You were born in Manila.

31:05.923 --> 31:06.697
-I'm sorry.
-(scoffs)

31:06.815 --> 31:08.423
I'll make this right somehow.

31:08.442 --> 31:10.350
How could you not know
how screwed up that is?

31:10.427 --> 31:12.685
So what? N-now I have to live
a life like you?

31:12.763 --> 31:13.778
I'll make this right.

31:13.931 --> 31:14.930
-How?
-Somehow.

31:14.948 --> 31:16.022
How the hell
can you make this right?

31:16.041 --> 31:17.432
I'll--I'll find a lawyer
or something.

31:17.451 --> 31:19.543
Right, right.
Working as a cleaning lady?

31:22.197 --> 31:24.197
Why don't you just stick
to messing up your own life?

31:24.216 --> 31:26.699
-Leave me the hell alone.
-Chris. Chris.

31:26.719 --> 31:28.427
I hate you!

31:30.372 --> 31:31.496
Chris.

31:31.648 --> 31:33.724
<i> (somber music)</i>

31:33.800 --> 31:36.101
(door slams)

31:37.545 --> 31:40.230
(door slams)

31:40.382 --> 31:44.309
(monitor beeping, door opens,
indistinct chatter)

31:44.461 --> 31:47.070
-Can I go in now?
-It's still touch and go.

31:47.222 --> 31:49.147
We've tried
a number of antibiotics

31:49.299 --> 31:52.725
and antiviral serums,
but they're not taking.

31:52.745 --> 31:54.894
What else can we do?

31:54.914 --> 31:56.988
We're still waiting on cultures
to determine what he has,

31:57.141 --> 31:59.917
but his liver's now
taken a hit.

32:00.110 --> 32:01.326
And if that fails,

32:01.478 --> 32:04.496
I'm--I'm afraid we have to
prepare for the worst.

32:04.572 --> 32:11.386
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:31.784 --> 32:35.077
(singing in Tagalog)

32:46.373 --> 32:49.257
(sobs softly)

32:52.638 --> 32:55.097
Sing again.

32:56.867 --> 32:59.868
Do your eyes hurt?

32:59.886 --> 33:02.295
Is that bad?

33:02.372 --> 33:03.888
No.

33:03.965 --> 33:06.466
It means your body's
talking to Mommy.

33:06.485 --> 33:08.402
(intercom buzzes)

33:13.400 --> 33:17.736
He's got conjunctivitis, fever,
pneumonia, and now pink eye.

33:17.888 --> 33:20.222
It has to be adenovirus.
We have to treat him now.

33:20.224 --> 33:22.907
Treating adenovirus without
conformation is too risky.

33:23.060 --> 33:25.243
It could be toxic
to his liver, kidneys.

33:25.395 --> 33:28.079
Cidofovir has proven success
in immunocompromised children.

33:28.156 --> 33:30.156
But if we're wrong, he could
end up with organ failure.

33:30.208 --> 33:32.917
And if we wait,
he might not make it at all.

33:32.994 --> 33:40.142
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:49.010 --> 33:51.936
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

33:52.013 --> 33:59.161
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:12.051 --> 34:15.052
(indistinct shouting)

34:18.390 --> 34:20.057
HAYAK: And how many times
have I told you that?

34:20.133 --> 34:21.950
ARMAN:
Hayak, come on.

34:21.952 --> 34:23.501
You went back
to Theo's warehouse

34:23.653 --> 34:24.728
after I told you not to.

34:24.805 --> 34:26.879
Then I find out
from Dr. Saroyan

34:26.899 --> 34:29.124
that you took her
to his clinic.

34:29.126 --> 34:31.050
He's our doctor
to take care of our family.

34:31.128 --> 34:33.904
Her son was dying, Hayak.
I had to do something--

34:34.055 --> 34:36.314
This is about my son!

34:36.466 --> 34:39.317
You do what I tell you!

34:39.394 --> 34:41.227
She didn't see anything
at the warehouse.

34:41.246 --> 34:43.305
You're gonna have to
trust me on this, Hayak.

34:43.323 --> 34:45.082
Look, she's not gonna
be any trouble.

34:45.158 --> 34:47.976
If I have to take care of her,
I'll do it myself.

34:47.978 --> 34:51.755
That is my call.
Not yours.

34:51.832 --> 34:54.424
You have a soft spot
for this woman.

34:54.576 --> 34:56.151
I'll take care of it.

34:56.211 --> 34:57.910
I didn't do--
I didn't say anything.

34:57.930 --> 35:01.014
I swear, I just
cleaned up after.

35:05.938 --> 35:09.497
But I-I did see
something here today.

35:09.516 --> 35:16.095
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:16.173 --> 35:20.675
A man was loading boxes
on one of your trucks.

35:20.694 --> 35:23.528
He looked nervous
like he was doing something

35:23.680 --> 35:25.622
he should not be doing.

35:25.699 --> 35:28.016
What did he look like?

35:28.018 --> 35:32.278
He had a-a round face
with a beard,

35:32.297 --> 35:35.781
red shirt, not very tall.

35:35.801 --> 35:38.360
It could be Jimmy.

35:38.378 --> 35:41.638
He was just in the loading bay
as we drove up.

35:41.715 --> 35:48.520
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:51.483 --> 35:53.400
(growls softly)

35:59.491 --> 36:01.324
(door opens)

36:05.055 --> 36:07.313
-ARMAN: Jimmy.
-(door closes)

36:07.332 --> 36:09.666
Jimmy.

36:09.817 --> 36:11.726
Were you heading out?

36:11.745 --> 36:13.745
Arman, hey.

36:13.821 --> 36:18.324
Yeah, heading to Reno
with this load, then back home.

36:18.343 --> 36:21.827
Hey, Jimmy, why don't you
give it to me straight?

36:21.905 --> 36:23.071
What is it?
What?

36:23.089 --> 36:24.330
Are we not paying you enough,

36:24.408 --> 36:25.907
or we're not treating
you right?

36:25.926 --> 36:28.410
Arman, no.

36:28.428 --> 36:31.337
Then how is it we're missing
some merchandise, Jimmy?

36:31.356 --> 36:32.856
I don't know
what you're talking about.

36:32.933 --> 36:36.276
Half a truckload of AKs
and AR-15s.

36:38.922 --> 36:41.156
You made
a big mistake, Jimmy.

36:42.868 --> 36:45.285
Arman, please.

36:49.599 --> 36:51.958
I never took nothing
from you before.

36:54.046 --> 36:57.272
And, what, you're going
to shoot me now?

36:57.274 --> 36:59.424
That's what you want to do?
You want to shoot me?

37:01.703 --> 37:03.970
Come on, shoot.

37:11.396 --> 37:14.064
No one steals from us, Jimmy.

37:15.717 --> 37:17.550
You understand me?
Nobody steals from us!

37:17.569 --> 37:20.570
(blows landing)

37:20.722 --> 37:23.631
(gunshots)

37:23.692 --> 37:30.163
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:43.262 --> 37:46.078
She was right.
Jimmy had our guns.

37:46.098 --> 37:47.989
Now we can close
this deal with Viktor

37:47.991 --> 37:50.267
and move on
to the hotel offer.

37:51.995 --> 37:54.145
I told you we could trust her.

38:01.671 --> 38:05.006
Thank you for your loyalty.

38:05.025 --> 38:07.008
I hope your son recovers soon.

38:07.010 --> 38:14.165
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:25.195 --> 38:28.379
(indistinct chatter,
door opens)

38:28.532 --> 38:29.213
(door closes)

38:29.366 --> 38:31.123
Renée. Renée.
Hey. Wait up.

38:31.143 --> 38:33.959
Wait up.
Check this out.

38:33.979 --> 38:35.720
What's this?

38:35.797 --> 38:36.888
GARRETT: Boom.

38:36.964 --> 38:38.056
RENEE:
Is that Arman Morales?

38:38.132 --> 38:40.299
With Thony and her kid.

38:40.319 --> 38:42.043
They look pretty cozy,
don't they?

38:42.062 --> 38:44.546
-They really do.
-Mm-hmm.

38:44.564 --> 38:46.381
You think
they're sleeping together?

38:46.399 --> 38:48.992
Well, whatever it is,
she lied to us,

38:49.069 --> 38:51.069
which means
she's protecting him.

38:51.221 --> 38:53.145
Okay. Then explain
that grin on your face.

38:53.165 --> 38:55.332
I mean, after losing Theo,

38:55.483 --> 38:58.726
I thought we'd have zero chance
of getting anyone else inside.

38:58.745 --> 39:02.822
But Thony, she's already in.

39:02.841 --> 39:05.066
That's if you can turn her.

39:05.085 --> 39:06.084
Piece of cake.

39:06.236 --> 39:08.127
And not break
every rule doing it.

39:08.238 --> 39:10.405
(groans)
Oh, God.

39:10.423 --> 39:13.074
I can't wait to hear how she's
gonna explain this away, huh?

39:13.093 --> 39:15.518
Ooh.
Neither can I.

39:15.595 --> 39:19.747
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

39:19.766 --> 39:23.418
(door opens)

39:23.436 --> 39:27.697
Well, you were right.
It was adenovirus.

39:27.849 --> 39:29.849
He's stabilizing now.

39:29.868 --> 39:31.868
I can't say he's out
of the woods just yet.

39:31.945 --> 39:34.929
But I feel he's past
the worst of it.

39:34.948 --> 39:37.874
Thank you, Dr. Saroyan.

39:37.951 --> 39:40.693
You're the one
who saved his life, Doctor.

39:40.770 --> 39:43.713
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:43.865 --> 39:47.550
(door opens, closes)

39:49.036 --> 39:52.305
(sighs)

39:55.619 --> 39:58.228
How--how much longer are they
going to keep him there?

39:58.379 --> 40:00.138
<i> THONY:</i>
<i> Just until the symptoms clear</i>

40:00.290 --> 40:02.548
<i> and he can breathe better.</i>

40:02.567 --> 40:07.153
But--but--but
he's gonna be okay, right?

40:09.299 --> 40:12.158
He almost didn't make it, Fi.

40:13.060 --> 40:15.987
But he did, Thony.

40:16.139 --> 40:19.165
And you--you made sure of that.

40:21.068 --> 40:24.996
It's not fair for him
to live like this.

40:25.148 --> 40:27.331
He's been through so much.

40:27.408 --> 40:29.575
<i> FIONA:</i>
<i> W-we'll make it through this.</i>

40:29.594 --> 40:31.836
We always do, right?

40:31.988 --> 40:39.102
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:40.254 --> 40:42.397
Thanks, Fi.
I love you. Bye.

40:45.168 --> 40:48.945
-ARMAN: You all right?
-(Thony sniffles)

40:49.096 --> 40:51.531
What I said
got that man killed.

40:53.510 --> 40:55.601
No, it's not on you.
He stole from us.

40:55.679 --> 40:58.246
He wasn't gonna
get away with that.

41:01.126 --> 41:03.418
And what matters is you
proved yourself to Hayak.

41:06.298 --> 41:10.508
You're gonna be all right.
And so will your son.

41:11.861 --> 41:13.878
THONY: Luca!

41:14.030 --> 41:17.474
(tapping on glass)

41:18.960 --> 41:22.053
(scoffs)

41:22.205 --> 41:25.464
<i> (uplifting music)</i>

41:25.542 --> 41:29.152
But you need to know--
once you're in, you're in.

41:29.229 --> 41:31.529
That's the way Hayak sees it.

41:35.827 --> 41:37.885
You understand?

41:37.904 --> 41:45.126
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
